<b>Check-in</b> will be 5 minutes before the event starts. In case someone is missing, reserves jump in.</p><br>

<h3><b>3. Session rules</b></h3> <br>
<h5><b>3.1 Qualifications</b></h5> <br>
<p><b>3.1.1</b> Track your map if you are in <b>OUT Lap</b>. Move aside if you see someone is incoming on a
fast lap. Driver will get 5 penalty points for breaking this rule. Repeating this incident will
result in 10 penalty points.<br><br>
<b>3.1.2</b> Not permitted to drive in <b>LOW FUEL MODE</b> more than the last sector on return to pit. Not
allowed to cut corners to save tires. Drivers will get 2 penalty points for breaking these rules.<br><br>
<b>3.1.3 </b><b>&#776; Retire car &#776;</b> on the track at the end of qualies is not allowed because maybe someone is
in fast lap and AI can affect his lap. Drivers will get 5 penalty points for breaking this rule.<br><br>
<b>3.1.4</b> Lobby restarts in case of technical issues.<br><br>
<b>3.1.5</b> In the case of <b>&#776; Host Migration &#776;</b> lobby is restarting right away.<br><br>
<b>3.1.6</b> In case someone joins the session later there is a possibility he will start the race at the
back of the grid. Qualification sessions will not be restarted.</p><br><br>

<h5><b>3.2 Race</b></h5> <br>
<p><b>3.2.1</b> Top 10 on the grid <b>MUST</b> start the race on the component which they used to set the fastest
lap. If a driver starts with a different component, he must pit in the first lap to change tires
otherwise he will be DSQ from the race and he will receive <b>5 penalty points</b>.
In this case compounds from the start will not be counted so driver must change at least 1
more different component until the end of the race.<br><br>
<b>3.2.2</b> All drivers must use 2 different components in one race.<br><br>
<b>3.2.3 </b> In case of rain conditions drivers can choose any tire compound.<br><br>
<b>3.2.4 </b> In case of <b>desync</b> for 3 or more drivers, the race restarts with the same order from the
qualifications. Drivers are obligated to start the race on the same tire compound as in the
broken lobby.<br><br>
<b>3.2.5 </b> In case of <b>massive collision on race start</b>, if 8 or more cars are retired race will be
restarted<br><br>
<b>3.2.6 </b> In case of technical issues if the race is <b>75% completed</b> the race will be finished and results
will be captured from the moment when the bug occurred.<br><br>
<b>3.2.7 </b> If race restart occurs for any reason, if the driver didn &#787;t choose a team at the new lobby he
will start the race from the back. <br><br>
<b>3.2.8 </b> If you want to leave the session <b>you must return the car to pit and retire</b>. If you retire on
track your car will create problems for other drivers in case of VSC and other. Penalty for
retiring a car on the track will be 10 penalty points. In case of technical issues, you will get
an additional invite so you can drive your car into the pits. In case of serious network error,
you are obligated to take a screenshot of the error and send it to KZRT after the race.<br><br>
<b>3.2.9 </b> <b>Blue Flag</b> â€“ Follow the Blue Flag instructions. KZRT can punish drivers with additional time
on their finish time for keeping leaders behind. In case a lapped car causes an accident,
the driver will face a minimum 1 or more race ban depending on the consequences on other
drivers.<br><br>
<b>3.2.10 </b> <b>Reset car</b> button is strongly forbidden. Resetting the car on track will result in post-race
DSQ. 10 penalty points will be added to the driver's license.</p><br><br>

