<h3><b>4. Driving etiquette</b></h3> <br>
<h5><b>4.1 Racing Rules</b></h5> <br>
<p><b>4.1.1 </b> On Race starts be <b>super careful</b>. Any sudden change of direction at the start is punishable.
You have to keep in mind that there are others besides you that you don't see. Be extra
careful at the start and think of others to avoid damage.<br><br>
<b>4.1.2 </b> <b>Causing an incident at the start</b> will result in a penalty from the KZRT.<br><br>
<b>4.1.3 </b> Any kind of <b>dive bombs</b> will be penalized even if they don &#787; t result in damage. KZRT will
support only clean overtakes. There are some places on the track where overtaking can be
very dangerous. Don &#787; t put yourself and other cars in a dangerous position. Try to overtake
the places where that can be done clean.<br><br>
<b>4.1.4 </b> Always <b>leave space for the other car</b>. In case another car has advantage of 1 &#823; 2 car length
you are obligated to leave him space in the corner. Not leaving space in described situations
will result in post-race penalties.<br><br>
<b>4.1.5</b> Any kind of <b>brake check</b> will be penalized with possible <b>DSQ</b>. KZRT will have to decide. <br><br>
<b>4.1.6 </b> <b>Deliberately causing the SC</b> will be post-race penalized by KZRT.<br><br>
<b>4.1.7 </b> <b>Deliberately crashing</b> in the race or after the race is strongly forbidden. 10 penalty points
will be added to the driver license for breaking this rule.<br><br>
<b>4.1.8 </b> It is not allowed to cross pit line entry and lit line exit. In case of &#779; <b>faking pit-stop</b> &#779; driver is
obligated not to cross pit line entry. This will be penalized even if game didn &#787; t give warning.<br><br>
<b>4.1.9 </b> It is strongly forbidden to destroy <b>breaking marks</b>. This will be tolerated only in case of
incident between two cars and if KZRT see driver couldn &#787; t avoid breaking mark.<br><br>
<b>4.1.10 </b> If you are involved in racing incident where you know you are fault for an incident, if
opponent doesn &#787; t have any damage you should be gentleman and you should give him the
position on the track. In these cases, KZRT will not give any time penalties or penalty points.</p><br><br>

<h5><b>4.2 Driving under yellow flags, SC and VSC</b></h5> <br>
<p><b>4.2.1 </b> If you come across a sector where there is a yellow flag, you are obliged to slow down. If
you run into an incident, you may be subject to investigation if you have not slowed down.
Overtaking under yellow flags is prohibited.<br><br>
<b>4.2.2 </b> In case of <b>VSC or DELTA</b> before SC drivers are obligated to stay within 2 seconds of Delta.
Massive slowdown will be punished by KZRT. Keeping others behind is restricted.<br><br>
<b>4.2.3 </b> Under <b>SC and VSC</b> circumstances any overtake is not allowed except the driver in front is
out from the track with all 4 wheels. Never follow the instructions given to you by the game.
Stay in your position, keep your distance from the driver in front of you.<br><br>
<b>4.2.4 </b> If <b>SC or VSC</b> occurs, if a driver hits someone from behind he will get penalized from the
game and penalization will not be removed. If a driver has been hit from behind and if he
gets 5s penalty from the game he can appeal.<br><br>
<b>4.2.5 </b> In case lappers are lapped and they cannot get back into the leader &#787; s lap, lapped drivers
are obligated to move aside on race restart. If there is a situation that behind the SC is the leader
of the race and behind him the drivers who are lagging behind for the whole lap, those drivers must
move to the side immediately on the race restart in order to be immediately overtaken by the others
and not to affect the race. It is not allowed to overtake between the drivers who are lagging behind
for the whole lap until the leaders who are close overtake them.</p><br><br>

